ve occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nLogoff records user logoffs. If this is an interactive logoff, it is recorded on the local system. If it is to a network share, it is recorded on the system accessed.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000472-GPOS-00217, SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-93171","SV-103259","CCI-000172","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5896","uuid":"b3cba1d4-6fa9-4052-9a30-2c7afed32b8f","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E1E14C7FFBE2267A4D3E5B629D100DCC4C7DD55E\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2019 must be configured to audit logoff successes.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205839","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205839","title":"SRG-OS-000474-GPOS-00219","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205839","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000474-GPOS-00219","rule_id_src":"SV-205839r991583_rule","rule_id":"SV-205839","rule_version":"WN19-AU-000130","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 must be configured to audit Detailed Tracking - Plug and Play Events successes.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Detailed Tracking >> \"Audit PNP Activity\" with \"Success\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN19-SO-000050) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective. \n\nUse the \"AuditPol\" tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\" or a \"Command Prompt\" with elevated privileges (\"Run as administrator\").\n\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\"\n\nCompare the \"AuditPol\" settings with the following:\n\nIf the system does not audit the following, this is a finding.\n\nDetailed Tracking >> Plug and Play Events - Success","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nPlug and Play activity records events related to the successful connection of external devices.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-93157","SV-103245","CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"9148","uuid":"928bcae1-bfdd-4ab4-9ca3-12fce39640a2","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 630DD0AE5EB8B305E4822896806172FA1EF29B7A\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2019 must be configured to audit Detailed Tracking - Plug and Play Events successes.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205840","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205840","title":"SRG-OS-000474-GPOS-00219","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205840","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000474-GPOS-00219","rule_id_src":"SV-205840r991583_rule","rule_id":"SV-205840","rule_version":"WN19-AU-000240","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 must be configured to audit Object Access - Removable Storage successes.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Object Access >> \"Audit Removable Storage\" with \"Success\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN19-SO-000050) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective. \n\nUse the \"AuditPol\" tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\" or a \"Command Prompt\" with elevated privileges (\"Run as administrator\").\n\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\"\n\nCompare the \"AuditPol\" settings with the following:\n\nIf the system does not audit the following, this is a finding.\n\nObject Access >> Removable Storage - Success\n\nVirtual machines or systems that use network attached storage may generate excessive audit events for secondary virtual drives or the network attached storage when this setting is enabled. This may be set to Not Configured in such cases and would not be a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nRemovable Storage auditing under Object Access records events related to access attempts on file system objects on removable storage devices.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-103255","V-93167","CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"8159","uuid":"c5f78604-da0a-4ca7-835c-04a02069af42","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 6EEE762FEBF47223403661AE054F416FCE6EB25B\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2019 must be configured to audit Object Access - Removable Storage successes.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205841","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205841","title":"SRG-OS-000474-GPOS-00219","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205841","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000474-GPOS-00219","rule_id_src":"SV-205841r991583_rule","rule_id":"SV-205841","rule_version":"WN19-AU-000250","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 must be configured to audit Object Access - Removable Storage failures.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Object Access >> \"Audit Removable Storage\" with \"Failure\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN19-SO-000050) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective. \n\nUse the \"AuditPol\" tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\" or a \"Command Prompt\" with elevated privileges (\"Run as administrator\").\n\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\"\n\nCompare the \"AuditPol\" settings with the following:\n\nIf the system does not audit the following, this is a finding.\n\nObject Access >> Removable Storage - Failure\n\nVirtual machines or systems that use network attached storage may generate excessive audit events for secondary virtual drives or the network attached storage when this setting is enabled. This may be set to Not Configured in such cases and would not be a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nRemovable Storage auditing under Object Access records events related to access attempts on file system objects on removable storage devices.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-103257","V-93169","CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"1964","uuid":"73664951-ac87-4ed8-b17c-d3231deda40b","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DDB40CB2FF0B7108EC8BD3009E2D08D4D9ED2F41\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2019 must be configured to audit Object Access - Removable Storage failures.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205842","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205842","title":"SRG-OS-000478-GPOS-00223","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205842","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000478-GPOS-00223","rule_id_src":"SV-205842r1137699_rule","rule_id":"SV-205842","rule_version":"WN19-SO-000360","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 must be configured to use FIPS-compliant algorithms for encryption, hashing, and signing.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"System cryptography: Use FIPS compliant algorithms for encryption, hashing, and signing\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is NA if the host is running SharePoint.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\FIPSAlgorithmPolicy\\\n\nValue Name: Enabled\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)\n \nClients with this setting enabled will not be able to communicate via digitally encrypted or signed protocols with servers that do not support these algorithms. Both the browser and web server must be configured to use TLS; otherwise. the browser will not be able to connect to a secure site.\n\nIf the server is hosting SharePoint, this is not applicable.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting ensures the system uses algorithms that are FIPS-compliant for encryption, hashing, and signing. FIPS-compliant algorithms meet specific standards established by the U.S. Government and must be the algorithms used for all OS encryption functions.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-103597","V-93511","CCI-002450"],"reference_identifier":"9980","uuid":"00ccfe86-c62f-4fd0-a5bb-70065e98afa7","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4E251FD6039E40319E28222D8F1B6C9C35FDC686\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2019 must be configured to use FIPS-compliant algorithms for encryption, hashing, and signing.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205843","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205843","title":"SRG-OS-000479-GPOS-00224","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205843","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000479-GPOS-00224","rule_id_src":"SV-205843r959008_rule","rule_id":"SV-205843","rule_version":"WN19-AU-000020","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 must, at a minimum, offload audit records of interconnected systems in real time and offload standalone or nondomain-joined systems weekly.","fix_text":"Configure the system to, at a minimum, offload audit records of interconnected systems in real time and offload standalone or nondomain-joined systems weekly.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the audit records, at a minimum, are offloaded for interconnected systems in real time and offloaded for standalone or nondomain-joined systems weekly. \n\nIf they are not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Protection of log data includes ensuring the log data is not accidentally lost or deleted. Audit information stored in one location is vulnerable to accidental or incidental deletion or alteration.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-103273","V-93185","CCI-001851"],"reference_identifier":"7473","uuid":"63ae65e9-cbbe-4fd2-a0fb-c66527ad6597","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-205844","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205844","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205844","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205844r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205844","rule_version":"WN19-00-000010","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 users with Administrative privileges must have separate accounts for administrative duties and normal operational tasks.","fix_text":"Ensure each user with administrative privileges has a separate account for user duties and one for privileged duties.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify each user with administrative privileges has been assigned a unique administrative account separate from their standard user account. \n\nIf users with administrative privileges do not have separate accounts for administrative functions and standard user functions, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Using a privileged account to perform routine functions makes the computer vulnerable to malicious software inadvertently introduced during a session that has been granted full privileges.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-93369","SV-103457","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"2024","uuid":"ee7f5ab2-aaa5-45ba-8cdf-3b2a69b91f1f","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: BDCA834F566F58B7169D4EF4AB71CEF89FBE164C\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2019 users with Administrative privileges must have separate accounts for administrative duties and normal operational tasks.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205845","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205845","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205845","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205845r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205845","rule_version":"WN19-00-000030","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 administrative accounts must not be used with applications that access the Internet, such as web browsers, or with potential Internet sources, such as email.","fix_text":"Establish a policy, at minimum, to prohibit administrative accounts from using applications that access the Internet, such as web browsers, or with potential Internet sources, such as email. Ensure the policy is enforced.\n\nThe organization may use technical means such as whitelisting to prevent the use of browsers and mail applications to enforce this requirement.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Determine whether organization policy, at a minimum, prohibits administrative accounts from using applications that access the Internet, such as web browsers, or with potential Internet sources, such as email, except as necessary for local service administration.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.\n\nThe organization may use technical means such as whitelisting to prevent the use of browsers and mail applications to enforce this requirement.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Using applications that access the Internet or have potential Internet sources using administrative privileges exposes a system to compromise. If a flaw in an application is exploited while running as a privileged user, the entire system could be compromised. Web browsers and email are common attack vectors for introducing malicious code and must not be run with an administrative account.\n\nSince administrative accounts may generally change or work around technical restrictions for running a web browser or other applications, it is essential that policy require administrative accounts to not access the Internet or use applications such as email.\n\nThe policy should define specific exceptions for local service administration. These exceptions may include HTTP(S)-based tools that are used for the administration of the local system, services, or attached devices.\n\nWhitelisting can be used to enforce the policy to ensure compliance.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-93205","SV-103293","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4617","uuid":"ba0c5986-8c62-463f-bffc-7d3fb304e72c","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 050714D49C476F58EDCB4F1B9ECBD5FADC2B5D01\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2019 administrative accounts must not be used with applications that access the Internet, such as web browsers, or with potential Internet sources, such as email.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205846","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205846","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205846","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205846r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205846","rule_version":"WN19-00-000040","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 members of the Backup Operators group must have separate accounts for backup duties and normal operational tasks.","fix_text":"Ensure each member of the Backup Operators group has separate accounts for backup functions and standard user functions.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If no accounts are members of the Backup Operators group, this is NA.\n\nVerify users with accounts in the Backup Operators group have a separate user account for backup functions and for performing normal user tasks.\n\nIf users with accounts in the Backup Operators group do not have separate accounts for backup functions and standard user functions, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Backup Operators are able to read and write to any file in the system, regardless of the rights assigned to it. Backup and restore rights permit users to circumvent the file access restrictions present on NTFS disk drives for backup and restore purposes. Members of the Backup Operators group must have separate logon accounts for performing backup duties.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-93207","SV-103295","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1230","uuid":"99579f85-37b4-45f6-8e2a-ed273c2c3ffe","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A27C5F59980F56C24B107FC315990F1CC83053FA\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2019 members of the Backup Operators group must have separate accounts for backup duties and normal operational tasks.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205847","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205847","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205847","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205847r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205847","rule_version":"WN19-00-000060","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 manually managed application account passwords must be changed at least annually or when a system administrator with knowledge of the password leaves the organization.","fix_text":"Change passwords for manually managed application/service accounts at least annually or when an administrator with knowledge of the password leaves the organization.\n\nIt is recommended that system-managed service accounts be used whenever possible.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Determine if manually managed application/service accounts exist. If none exist, this is NA.\n\nIf passwords for manually managed application/service accounts are not changed at least annually or when an administrator with knowledge of the password leaves the organization, this is a finding.\n\nIdentify manually managed application/service accounts.\n\nTo determine the date a password was last changed:\n\nDomain controllers:\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\".\n\nEnter \"Get-AdUser -Identity [application account name] -Properties PasswordLastSet | FT Name, PasswordLastSet\", where [application account name] is the name of the manually managed application/service account.\n\nIf the \"PasswordLastSet\" date is more than one year old, this is a finding.\n\nMember servers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems:\n\nOpen \"Command Prompt\".\n\nEnter 'Net User [application account name] | Find /i \"Password Last Set\"', where [application account name] is the name of the manually managed application/service account.\n\nIf the \"Password Last Set\" date is more than one year old, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Setting application account passwords to expire may cause applications to stop functioning. However, not changing them on a regular basis exposes them to attack. If managed service accounts are used, this alleviates the need to manually change application account passwords.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-103297","V-93209","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1103","uuid":"2338a95e-20dd-41cc-85c5-41afeb2c2ff9","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 51074C333DDDECD78376497EA303BB0FB64F60FC\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2019 manually managed application account passwords must be changed at least annually or when a system administrator with knowledge of the password leaves the organization.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205848","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205848","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205848","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205848r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205848","rule_version":"WN19-00-000090","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 domain-joined systems must have a Trusted Platform Module (TPM) enabled and ready for use.","fix_text":"Ensure domain-joined systems have a TPM that is configured for use. (Versions 2.0 or 1.2 support Credential Guard.)\n\nThe TPM must be enabled in the firmware.\n\nRun \"tpm.msc\" for configuration options in Windows.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"For standalone or nondomain-joined systems, this is NA.\n\nVerify the system has a TPM and it is ready for use.\n\nRun \"tpm.msc\".\n\nReview the sections in the center pane.\n\n\"Status\" must indicate it has been configured with a message such as \"The TPM is ready for use\" or \"The TPM is on and ownership has been taken\".\n\nTPM Manufacturer Information - Specific Version = 2.0 or 1.2\n\nIf a TPM is not found or is not ready for use, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Credential Guard uses virtualization-based security to protect data that could be used in credential theft attacks if compromised. A number of system requirements must be met in order for Credential Guard to be configured and enabled properly. Without a TPM enabled and ready for use, Credential Guard keys are stored in a less secure method using software.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-93213","SV-103301","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9311","uuid":"1c5ef978-92e7-4396-b2bd-919442517b86","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F8F86791196ED9788C90B7387D2AB50CD5A01D43\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2019 domain-joined systems must have a Trusted Platform Module (TPM) enabled and ready for use.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205849","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205849","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205849","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205849r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205849","rule_version":"WN19-00-000100","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 must be maintained at a supported servicing level.","fix_text":"Update the system to a Version 1809 (Build 17763.xxx) or greater.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Open \"Command Prompt\".\n\nEnter \"winver.exe\".\n\nIf the \"About Windows\" dialog box does not display \"Microsoft Windows Server Version 1809 (Build 17763.xxx)\" or greater, this is a finding.\n\nPreview versions must not be used in a production environment.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Systems at unsupported servicing levels will not receive security updates for new vulnerabilities, which leave them subject to exploitation. Systems must be maintained at a servicing level supported by the vendor with new security updates.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-103303","V-93215","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"2974","uuid":"76b2bb80-6afb-4467-a0a2-52fa6d9490e0","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DAC6459B39176F831BB495EBC836C68BC74FDCAB\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Windows Server 2019 must be maintained at a supported servicing level.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205850","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205850","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205850","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205850r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205850","rule_version":"WN19-00-000110","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 must use an anti-virus program.","fix_text":"If no anti-virus software is in use, install Windows Defender or third-party anti-virus.\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\".\n\nEnter \"Install-WindowsFeature -Name Windows-Defender\u201d.\n\nFor third-party anti-virus, install per anti-virus instructions and disable Windows Defender.\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\".\n\nEnter \"Uninstall-WindowsFeature -Name Windows-Defender\u201d.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify an anti-virus solution is installed on the system. The anti-virus solution may be bundled with an approved host-based security solution.\n\nIf there is no anti-virus solution installed on the system, this is a finding.\n\nVerify if Windows Defender is in use or enabled:\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\".\n\nEnter \u201cget-service | where {$_.DisplayName -Like \"*Defender*\"} | Select Status,DisplayName\u201d\n\nVerify if third-party anti-virus is in use or enabled:\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\".\n\nEnter \"get-service | where {$_.DisplayName -Like \"*mcafee*\"} | Select Status,DisplayName\u201d\n\nEnter \"get-service | where {$_.DisplayName -Like \"*symantec*\"} | Select Status,DisplayName\u201d","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Malicious software can establish a base on individual desktops and servers. Employing an automated mechanism to detect this type of software will aid in elimination of the software from the operating system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-103305","V-93217","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"8565","uuid":"97d4fa34-3856-4306-a0a6-c41de329aa5a","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: BED925BDD6B79C91053024066B8ABD633E9260C7\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2019 must use an anti-virus program.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205851","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205851","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205851","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205851r1186378_rule","rule_id":"SV-205851","rule_version":"WN19-00-000120","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 must have a host-based intrusion detection and prevention service installed.","fix_text":"Install a HIDS and HIPS on each server.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Determine if there is a HIDS and HIPS on each server. \n\nA HIDS device is not required on a system that has the role as the Network Intrusion Device (NID). However, this exception needs to be documented with the information system security officer (ISSO).\n\nIf a HIDS and HIPS are not installed on the system, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A properly configured Host-based Intrusion Detection System (HIDS) and Host-based Intrusion Prevention System (HIPS) provides another level of defense against unauthorized access to critical servers. With proper configuration and logging enabled, such a system can stop and/or alert for many attempts to gain unauthorized access to resources.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-103307","V-93219","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"8343","uuid":"982676dc-51b6-4f5c-8e17-5b141e136f50","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D69A66B93C9972D9928058C2CBDD92797344D46A\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2019 must have a host-based intrusion detection and prevention service installed.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205852","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205852","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205852","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205852r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205852","rule_version":"WN19-00-000240","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 must have software certificate installation files removed.","fix_text":"Remove any certificate installation files (*.p12 and *.pfx) found on a system.\n\nNote: This does not apply to server-based applications that have a requirement for .p12 certificate files or Adobe PreFlight certificate files.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Search all drives for *.p12 and *.pfx files.\n\nIf any files with these extensions exist, this is a finding.\n\nThis does not apply to server-based applications that have a requirement for .p12 certificate files or Adobe PreFlight certificate files. Some applications create files with extensions of .p12 that are not certificate installation files. Removal of non-certificate installation files from systems is not required. These must be documented with the ISSO.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Use of software certificates and their accompanying installation files for end users to access resources is less secure than the use of hardware-based certificates.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-93221","SV-103309","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"8280","uuid":"1f809f31-d5ec-4502-9926-c169b9a8eda8","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-205853","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205853","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205853","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205853r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205853","rule_version":"WN19-00-000420","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 FTP servers must be configured to prevent anonymous logons.","fix_text":"Configure the FTP service to prevent anonymous logons.\n\nOpen \"Internet Information Services (IIS) Manager\".\n\nSelect the server.\n\nDouble-click \"FTP Authentication\".\n\nSelect \"Anonymous Authentication\".\n\nSelect \"Disabled\" under \"Actions\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If FTP is not installed on the system, this is NA.\n\nOpen \"Internet Information Services (IIS) Manager\".\n\nSelect the server.\n\nDouble-click \"FTP Authentication\".\n\nIf the \"Anonymous Authentication\" status is \"Enabled\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The FTP service allows remote users to access shared files and directories. Allowing anonymous FTP connections makes user auditing difficult.\n\nUsing accounts that have administrator privileges to log on to FTP risks that the userid and password will be captured on the network and give administrator access to an unauthorized user.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-93223","SV-103311","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"6677","uuid":"889d7769-6a46-4c3d-bef6-9c6b2767205c","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 042B53C512254C3472D8BE065A81DE2BF5592AEF\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2019 FTP servers must be configured to prevent anonymous logons.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205854","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205854","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205854","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205854r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205854","rule_version":"WN19-00-000430","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 FTP servers must be configured to prevent access to the system drive.","fix_text":"Configure the FTP sites to allow access only to specific FTP shared resources. Do not allow access to other areas of the system.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If FTP is not installed on the system, this is NA.\n\nOpen \"Internet Information Services (IIS) Manager\".\n\nSelect \"Sites\" under the server name.\n\nFor any sites with a Binding that lists FTP, right-click the site and select \"Explore\".\n\nIf the site is not defined to a specific folder for shared FTP resources, this is a finding.\n\nIf the site includes any system areas such as root of the drive, Program Files, or Windows directories, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The FTP service allows remote users to access shared files and directories that could provide access to system resources and compromise the system, especially if the user can gain access to the root directory of the boot drive.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-93225","SV-103313","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"8255","uuid":"c73e7e52-b1b0-4fa0-a53e-bf7a98adfdc1","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F89E0F3252081D19299B701722E6FC1AC55D83F6\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2019 FTP servers must be configured to prevent access to the system drive.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205855","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205855","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205855","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205855r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205855","rule_version":"WN19-00-000450","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 must have orphaned security identifiers (SIDs) removed from user rights.","fix_text":"Remove any unresolved SIDs found in User Rights assignments and determined to not be for currently valid accounts or groups by removing the accounts or groups from the appropriate group policy.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Review the effective User Rights setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nReview each User Right listed for any unresolved SIDs to determine whether they are valid, such as due to being temporarily disconnected from the domain. (Unresolved SIDs have the format that begins with \"*S-1-\".)\n\nIf any unresolved SIDs exist and are not for currently valid accounts or groups, this is a finding.\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /export /areas USER_RIGHTS /cfg c:\\path\\UserRights.txt\n\nThe results in the file identify user right assignments by SID instead of group name. Review the SIDs for unidentified ones. A list of typical SIDs \\ Groups is below, search Microsoft for articles on well-known SIDs for others. \n\nIf any unresolved SIDs exist and are not for currently valid accounts or groups, this is a finding.\n\nSID - Group\nS-1-5-11 - Authenticated Users\nS-1-5-113 - Local account\nS-1-5-114 - Local account and member of Administrators group\nS-1-5-19 - Local Service\nS-1-5-20 - Network Service\nS-1-5-32-544 - Administrators\nS-1-5-32-546 - Guests\nS-1-5-6 - Service\nS-1-5-9 - Enterprise Domain Controllers\nS-1-5-domain-512 - Domain Admins\nS-1-5-root domain-519 - Enterprise Admins\nS-1-5-80-3139157870-2983391045-3678747466-658725712-1809340420 - NT Service\\WdiServiceHost","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Accounts or groups given rights on a system may show up as unresolved SIDs for various reasons including deletion of the accounts or groups.  If the account or group objects are reanimated, there is a potential they may still have rights no longer intended.  Valid domain accounts or groups may also show up as unresolved SIDs if a connection to the domain cannot be established for some reason.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-93227","SV-103315","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4121","uuid":"5812a886-5711-4b14-bd57-699790a1c225","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 74A6983962C33EB1FF1542D47E91542AA1389F12\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2019 must have orphaned security identifiers (SIDs) removed from user rights.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205856","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205856","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205856","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205856r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205856","rule_version":"WN19-00-000460","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 systems must have Unified Extensible Firmware Interface (UEFI) firmware and be configured to run in UEFI mode, not Legacy BIOS.","fix_text":"Configure UEFI firmware to run in \"UEFI\" mode, not \"Legacy BIOS\" mode.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Some older systems may not have UEFI firmware. This is currently a CAT III; it will be raised in severity at a future date when broad support of Windows hardware and firmware requirements are expected to be met. Devices that have UEFI firmware must run in \"UEFI\" mode.\n\nVerify the system firmware is configured to run in \"UEFI\" mode, not \"Legacy BIOS\".\n\nRun \"System Information\".\n\nUnder \"System Summary\", if \"BIOS Mode\" does not display \"UEFI\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"UEFI provides additional security features in comparison to legacy BIOS firmware, including Secure Boot. UEFI is required to support additional security features in Windows, including Virtualization Based Security and Credential Guard. Systems with UEFI that are operating in \"Legacy BIOS\" mode will not support these security features.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-93229","SV-103317","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"2194","uuid":"be92460a-2f7d-4a42-8ae6-b62a65b31dd9","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2493678CE5DAD12E3042C98B976AB3ED77F3DBC3\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2019 systems must have Unified Extensible Firmware Interface (UEFI) firmware and be configured to run in UEFI mode, not Legacy BIOS.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205857","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205857","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205857","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205857r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205857","rule_version":"WN19-00-000470","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 must have Secure Boot enabled.","fix_text":"Enable Secure Boot in the system firmware.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Some older systems may not have UEFI firmware. This is currently a CAT III; it will be raised in severity at a future date when broad support of Windows hardware and firmware requirements are expected to be met. Devices that have UEFI firmware must have Secure Boot enabled.  \n\nRun \"System Information\".\n\nUnder \"System Summary\", if \"Secure Boot State\" does not display \"On\", this is a finding.\n\nOn server core installations, run the following PowerShell command:\n\nConfirm-SecureBootUEFI\n\nIf a value of \"True\" is not returned, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Secure Boot is a standard that ensures systems boot only to a trusted operating system. Secure Boot is required to support additional security features in Windows, including Virtualization Based Security and Credential Guard. If Secure Boot is turned off, these security features will not function.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-103319","V-93231","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"8197","uuid":"05395393-2213-424e-b96c-0d9fea4cb999","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 801E9685D597CE9D174FC9D24B2A660978A0A2FC\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Windows Server 2019 must have Secure Boot enabled.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205858","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205858","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205858","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205858r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205858","rule_version":"WN19-CC-000030","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 Internet Protocol version 6 (IPv6) source routing must be configured to the highest protection level to prevent IP source routing.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> MSS (Legacy) >> \"MSS: (DisableIPSourceRouting IPv6) IP source routing protection level (protects against packet spoofing)\" to \"Enabled\" with \"Highest protection, source routing is completely disabled\" selected.\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the MSS-Legacy custom templates included with the STIG package. \"MSS-Legacy.admx\" and \"MSS-Legacy.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories respectively.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Tcpip6\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: DisableIPSourceRouting\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000002 (2)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Configuring the system to disable IPv6 source routing protects against spoofing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-103321","V-93233","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"3848","uuid":"a81dc0d4-741a-4914-901f-a7cc9f5c362c","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-205859","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205859","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205859","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205859r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205859","rule_version":"WN19-CC-000040","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 source routing must be configured to the highest protection level to prevent Internet Protocol (IP) source routing.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> MSS (Legacy) >> \"MSS: (DisableIPSourceRouting) IP source routing protection level (protects against packet spoofing)\" to \"Enabled\" with \"Highest protection, source routing is completely disabled\" selected.\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the MSS-Legacy custom templates included with the STIG package. \"MSS-Legacy.admx\" and \"MSS-Legacy.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories respectively.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Tcpip\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: DisableIPSourceRouting\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000002 (2)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Configuring the system to disable IP source routing protects against spoofing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-103323","V-93235","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"8461","uuid":"beff96e8-04ba-41fc-b0bf-1e6fb8c7ba53","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: AFBB6E1E008B183429BF68A8EE827D4D00D97768\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2019 source routing must be configured to the highest protection level to prevent Internet Protocol (IP) source routing.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205860","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205860","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205860","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205860r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205860","rule_version":"WN19-CC-000050","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 must be configured to prevent Internet Control Message Protocol (ICMP) redirects from overriding Open Shortest Path First (OSPF)-generated routes.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> MSS (Legacy) >> \"MSS: (EnableICMPRedirect) Allow ICMP redirects to override OSPF generated routes\" to \"Disabled\".\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the MSS-Legacy custom templates included with the STIG package. \"MSS-Legacy.admx\" and \"MSS-Legacy.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories respectively.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Tcpip\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: EnableICMPRedirect\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing ICMP redirect of routes can lead to traffic not being routed properly. When disabled, this forces ICMP to be routed via the shortest path first.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-103325","V-93237","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5250","uuid":"6d23fb35-3a46-4d3e-b126-7f484fc68841","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: BFBAC894BA3C59347E4D86DCDD0D8F13DE10E5E1\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2019 must be configured to prevent Internet Control Message Protocol (ICMP) redirects from overriding Open Shortest Path First (OSPF)-generated routes.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205861","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205861","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205861","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205861r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205861","rule_version":"WN19-CC-000070","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 insecure logons to an SMB server must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Network >> Lanman Workstation >> \"Enable insecure guest logons\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\LanmanWorkstation\\\n\nValue Name: AllowInsecureGuestAuth\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Insecure guest logons allow unauthenticated access to shared folders. Shared resources on a system must require authentication to establish proper access.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-103327","V-93239","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4686","uuid":"4ff56fc3-9de1-4483-9bb1-2ce5a8d9cfd5","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C49A857FB90C123C3C54F12E3D2950D2DB960B6B\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2019 insecure logons to an SMB server must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205862","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205862","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205862","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205862r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205862","rule_version":"WN19-CC-000080","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 hardened Universal Naming Convention (UNC) paths must be defined to require mutual authentication and integrity for at least the \\\\*\\SYSVOL and \\\\*\\NETLOGON shares.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Network >> Network Provider >> \"Hardened UNC Paths\" to \"Enabled\" with at least the following configured in \"Hardened UNC Paths\" (click the \"Show\" button to display):\n\nValue Name: \\\\*\\SYSVOL\nValue: RequireMutualAuthentication=1, RequireIntegrity=1\n\nValue Name: \\\\*\\NETLOGON\nValue: RequireMutualAuthentication=1, RequireIntegrity=1","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This requirement is applicable to domain-joined systems. For standalone or nondomain-joined systems, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry values do not exist or are not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\NetworkProvider\\HardenedPaths\\\n\nValue Name: \\\\*\\NETLOGON\nValue Type: REG_SZ\nValue: RequireMutualAuthentication=1, RequireIntegrity=1\n\nValue Name: \\\\*\\SYSVOL\nValue Type: REG_SZ\nValue: RequireMutualAuthentication=1, RequireIntegrity=1\n\nAdditional entries would not be a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Additional security requirements are applied to UNC paths specified in hardened UNC paths before allowing access to them. This aids in preventing tampering with or spoofing of connections to these paths.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-103329","V-93241","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4807","uuid":"7d4e5d88-1755-4e81-8d87-082fc1c5285f","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: B8A5E8B488AF82F76150D8750E14568DB95B6242\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2019 hardened Universal Naming Convention (UNC) paths must be defined to require mutual authentication and integrity for at least the \\\\*\\SYSVOL and \\\\*\\NETLOGON shares.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205863","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205863","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205863","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205863r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205863","rule_version":"WN19-CC-000100","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 must be configured to enable Remote host allows delegation of non-exportable credentials.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Credentials Delegation >> \"Remote host allows delegation of non-exportable credentials\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CredentialsDelegation\\\n\nValue Name: AllowProtectedCreds\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"An exportable version of credentials is provided to remote hosts when using credential delegation which exposes them to theft on the remote host.  Restricted Admin mode or Remote Credential Guard allow delegation of non-exportable credentials providing additional protection of the credentials.  Enabling this configures the host to support Restricted Admin mode or Remote Credential Guard.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-93243","SV-103331","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"2268","uuid":"e6e4500c-dfff-4c29-a61a-63434e578b83","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F068A5275983F531340EF036721E4E5A55A74558\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2019 must be configured to enable Remote host allows delegation of non-exportable credentials.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205864","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205864","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205864","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205864r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205864","rule_version":"WN19-CC-000110","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 virtualization-based security must be enabled with the platform security level configured to Secure Boot or Secure Boot with DMA Protection.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Device Guard >> \"Turn On Virtualization Based Security\" to \"Enabled\" with \"Secure Boot\" or \"Secure Boot and DMA Protection\" selected.\n\nA Microsoft TechNet article on Credential Guard, including system requirement details, can be found at the following link:\n\nhttps://technet.microsoft.com/itpro/windows/keep-secure/credential-guard","weight":"10.0","check_content":"For standalone or nondomain-joined systems, this is NA.\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\" with elevated privileges (run as administrator).\n\nEnter the following:\n\n\"Get-CimInstance -ClassName Win32_DeviceGuard -Namespace root\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DeviceGuard\"\n\nIf \"RequiredSecurityProperties\" does not include a value of \"2\" indicating \"Secure Boot\" (e.g., \"{1, 2}\"), this is a finding.\n\nIf \"Secure Boot and DMA Protection\" is configured, \"3\" will also be displayed in the results (e.g., \"{1, 2, 3}\").\n\nIf \"VirtualizationBasedSecurityStatus\" is not a value of \"2\" indicating \"Running\", this is a finding.\n\nAlternately:\n\nRun \"System Information\".\n\nUnder \"System Summary\", verify the following:\n\nIf \"Virtualization based security\" does not display \"Running\", this is a finding.\n\nIf \"Virtualization based Required security Properties\" does not display \"Base Virtualization Support, Secure Boot\", this is a finding.\n\nIf \"Secure Boot and DMA Protection\" is configured, \"DMA Protection\" will also be displayed (e.g., \"Base Virtualization Support, Secure Boot, DMA Protection\").\n\nThe policy settings referenced in the Fix section will configure the following registry values. However, due to hardware requirements, the registry values alone do not ensure proper function.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DeviceGuard\\\n\nValue Name: EnableVirtualizationBasedSecurity\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)\n\nValue Name: RequirePlatformSecurityFeatures\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1) (Secure Boot only) or 0x00000003 (3) (Secure Boot and DMA Protection)\n\nA Microsoft TechNet article on Credential Guard, including system requirement details, can be found at the following link:\n\nhttps://technet.microsoft.com/itpro/windows/keep-secure/credential-guard","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Virtualization-based security (VBS) provides the platform for the additional security features Credential Guard and virtualization-based protection of code integrity. Secure Boot is the minimum security level, with DMA protection providing additional memory protection. DMA Protection requires a CPU that supports input/output memory management unit (IOMMU).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-93245","SV-103333","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1181","uuid":"dbe71776-5727-45fa-b261-45ed6791adc7","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 706DF805ACBDF247F32F812B6861C4C845AACEB9\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2019 virtualization-based security must be enabled with the platform security level configured to Secure Boot or Secure Boot with DMA Protection.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205865","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205865","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205865","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205865r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205865","rule_version":"WN19-CC-000130","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 Early Launch Antimalware, Boot-Start Driver Initialization Policy must prevent boot drivers identified as bad.","fix_text":"The default behavior is for Early Launch Antimalware - Boot-Start Driver Initialization policy to enforce \"Good, unknown and bad but critical\" (preventing \"bad\").\n\nIf this needs to be corrected or a more secure setting is desired, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Early Launch Antimalware >> \"Boot-Start Driver Initialization Policy\" to \"Not Configured\" or \"Enabled\" with any option other than \"All\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The default behavior is for Early Launch Antimalware - Boot-Start Driver Initialization policy to enforce \"Good, unknown and bad but critical\" (preventing \"bad\").\n\nIf the registry value name below does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"0x00000007 (7)\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Policies\\EarlyLaunch\\\n\nValue Name: DriverLoadPolicy\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1), 0x00000003 (3), or 0x00000008 (8) (or if the Value Name does not exist)\n\nPossible values for this setting are:\n8 - Good only\n1 - Good and unknown\n3 - Good, unknown and bad but critical\n7 - All (which includes \"bad\" and would be a finding)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Compromised boot drivers can introduce malware prior to protection mechanisms that load after initialization. The Early Launch Antimalware driver can limit allowed drivers based on classifications determined by the malware protection application. At a minimum, drivers determined to be bad must not be allowed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-93249","SV-103337","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"6523","uuid":"19eecf45-794d-4e2f-a757-97712100aab1","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: EC97552A52D9CCDB2F86788096194095CC05EC96\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2019 Early Launch Antimalware, Boot-Start Driver Initialization Policy must prevent boot drivers identified as bad.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205866","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205866","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205866","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205866r1135352_rule","rule_id":"SV-205866","rule_version":"WN19-CC-000140","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 group policy objects must be reprocessed even if they have not changed.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Group Policy >> \"Configure registry policy processing\" to \"Enabled\" with the option \"Process even if the Group Policy objects have not changed\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This requirement is not applicable for Domain Controllers.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Group Policy\\{35378EAC-683F-11D2-A89A-00C04FBBCFA2}\\\n\nValue Name: NoGPOListChanges\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Registry entries for group policy settings can potentially be changed from the required configuration. This could occur as part of troubleshooting or by a malicious process on a compromised system. Enabling this setting and then selecting the \"Process even if the Group Policy objects have not changed\" option ensures the policies will be reprocessed even if none have been changed. This way, any unauthorized changes are forced to match the domain-based group policy settings again.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-93251","SV-103339","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"6312","uuid":"b22163df-857c-4a8b-a31c-9d7121d14919","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8FB3139CDC618A0063E5BDF91D5189A565F34C03\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2019 group policy objects must be reprocessed even if they have not changed.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205867","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205867","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205867","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205867r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205867","rule_version":"WN19-CC-000180","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 users must be prompted to authenticate when the system wakes from sleep (on battery).","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Power Management >> Sleep Settings >> \"Require a password when a computer wakes (on battery)\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Power\\PowerSettings\\0e796bdb-100d-47d6-a2d5-f7d2daa51f51\\\n\nValue Name: DCSettingIndex\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A system that does not require authentication when resuming from sleep may provide access to unauthorized users. Authentication must always be required when accessing a system. This setting ensures users are prompted for a password when the system wakes from sleep (on battery).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-93253","SV-103341","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4681","uuid":"91678905-9982-44a3-9dd0-63e182549479","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DBD72B56D6617481423559F175655CC82129F2DD\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Windows Server 2019 users must be prompted to authenticate when the system wakes from sleep (on battery).' is not present or not in use on this the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205868","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205868","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205868","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205868r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205868","rule_version":"WN19-CC-000190","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 users must be prompted to authenticate when the system wakes from sleep (plugged in).","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Power Management >> Sleep Settings >> \"Require a password when a computer wakes (plugged in)\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Power\\PowerSettings\\0e796bdb-100d-47d6-a2d5-f7d2daa51f51\\\n\nValue Name: ACSettingIndex\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A system that does not require authentication when resuming from sleep may provide access to unauthorized users. Authentication must always be required when accessing a system. This setting ensures users are prompted for a password when the system wakes from sleep (plugged in).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-93255","SV-103343","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4257","uuid":"81d08347-a39a-42d6-9eac-80c5f6ff9ee3","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 418C6256B298E2594389BF40389C0F1550405AA4\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2019 users must be prompted to authenticate when the system wakes from sleep (plugged in).' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205869","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205869","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205869","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205869r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205869","rule_version":"WN19-CC-000250","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 Telemetry must be configured to Security or Basic.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Data Collection >> \"Allow Telemetry\" to \"Enabled\" with \"0 - Security [Enterprise Only]\" or \"1 - Basic\" selected in \"Options\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DataCollection\\\n\nValue Name: AllowTelemetry\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0) (Security), 0x00000001 (1) (Basic)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature. Limiting this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise. The \"Security\" option for Telemetry configures the lowest amount of data, effectively none outside of the Malicious Software Removal Tool (MSRT), Defender, and telemetry client settings. \"Basic\" sends basic diagnostic and usage data and may be required to support some Microsoft services.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-103345","V-93257","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1622","uuid":"1bc00fba-7b89-44e4-8673-cd8e62755d06","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 49A2327827999ABEE4FB93BE04B79A4A814A0009\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2019 Telemetry must be configured to Security or Basic.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205870","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205870","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205870","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205870r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205870","rule_version":"WN19-CC-000260","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 Windows Update must not obtain updates from other PCs on the Internet.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Delivery Optimization >> \"Download Mode\" to \"Enabled\" with any option except \"Internet\" selected.\n\nAcceptable selections include:\n\nBypass (100)\nGroup (2)\nHTTP only (0)\nLAN (1)\nSimple (99)","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DeliveryOptimization\\\n\nValue Name: DODownloadMode\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0) - No peering (HTTP Only)\n0x00000001 (1) - Peers on same NAT only (LAN)\n0x00000002 (2) - Local Network / Private group peering (Group)\n0x00000063 (99) - Simple download mode, no peering (Simple)\n0x00000064 (100) - Bypass mode, Delivery Optimization not used (Bypass)\n\nA value of 0x00000003 (3), Internet, is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Windows Update can obtain updates from additional sources instead of Microsoft. In addition to Microsoft, updates can be obtained from and sent to PCs on the local network as well as on the Internet. This is part of the Windows Update trusted process, however to minimize outside exposure, obtaining updates from or sending to systems on the Internet must be prevented.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-103347","V-93259","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"7381","uuid":"e3b3fd25-5ca6-4959-9fb6-6c88e686e700","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 99F665BF02D312B9800690175FB4FDCFBF3F039C\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2019 Windows Update must not obtain updates from other PCs on the Internet.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205871","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205871","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205871","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205871r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205871","rule_version":"WN19-CC-000320","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 Turning off File Explorer heap termination on corruption must be disabled.","fix_text":"The default behavior is for File Explorer heap termination on corruption to be disabled.\n\nIf this needs to be corrected, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> File Explorer >> \"Turn off heap termination on corruption\" to \"Not Configured\" or \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The default behavior is for File Explorer heap termination on corruption to be enabled.\n\nIf the registry Value Name below does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"0\", this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"1\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: NoHeapTerminationOnCorruption\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0) (or if the Value Name does not exist)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Legacy plug-in applications may continue to function when a File Explorer session has become corrupt. Disabling this feature will prevent this.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-93261","SV-103349","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5126","uuid":"9bfa42b1-aa29-4f04-b38e-a790511cc02a","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 0175A0C4A81E585E5806463C420F26B77260B737\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2019 Turning off File Explorer heap termination on corruption must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205872","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205872","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205872","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205872r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205872","rule_version":"WN19-CC-000330","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 File Explorer shell protocol must run in protected mode.","fix_text":"The default behavior is for shell protected mode to be turned on for File Explorer.\n\nIf this needs to be corrected, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> File Explorer >> \"Turn off shell protocol protected mode\" to \"Not Configured\" or \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The default behavior is for shell protected mode to be turned on for File Explorer.\n\nIf the registry value name below does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"0\", this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"1\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: PreXPSP2ShellProtocolBehavior\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0) (or if the Value Name does not exist)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The shell protocol will limit the set of folders that applications can open when run in protected mode. Restricting files an application can open to a limited set of folders increases the security of Windows.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-93263","SV-103351","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"8807","uuid":"b4f2b262-c8ec-4b45-9765-4d8108d3d3b3","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: ADE76D7FF851B9979481C16389F6A44F17880CB4\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Windows Server 2019 File Explorer shell protocol must run in protected mode.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205873","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205873","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205873","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205873r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205873","rule_version":"WN19-CC-000390","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 must prevent attachments from being downloaded from RSS feeds.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> RSS Feeds >> \"Prevent downloading of enclosures\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Feeds\\\n\nValue Name: DisableEnclosureDownload\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Attachments from RSS feeds may not be secure. This setting will prevent attachments from being downloaded from RSS feeds.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-93265","SV-103353","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"2561","uuid":"7f6d7452-e63b-4814-bc2e-a380320faadb","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A2B0E53F47BDC628193F976F5FA0A5668CDFEFBD\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2019 must prevent attachments from being downloaded from RSS feeds.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205874","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205874","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205874","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205874r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205874","rule_version":"WN19-CC-000440","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 users must be notified if a web-based program attempts to install software.","fix_text":"The default behavior is for Internet Explorer to warn users and select whether to allow or refuse installation when a web-based program attempts to install software on the system.\n\nIf this needs to be corrected, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Installer >> \"Prevent Internet Explorer security prompt for Windows Installer scripts\" to \"Not Configured\" or \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The default behavior is for Internet Explorer to warn users and select whether to allow or refuse installation when a web-based program attempts to install software on the system.\n\nIf the registry value name below does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"0\", this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"1\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Installer\\\n\nValue Name: SafeForScripting\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0) (or if the Value Name does not exist)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Web-based programs may attempt to install malicious software on a system. Ensuring users are notified if a web-based program attempts to install software allows them to refuse the installation.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-103355","V-93267","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"6208","uuid":"db80fa64-6e3b-456d-87f7-f8b6328dee20","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C5E0FA2538EC5490B80846294D47C7B8DBE3B493\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2019 users must be notified if a web-based program attempts to install software.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205875","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205875","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205875","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205875r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205875","rule_version":"WN19-DC-000150","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 directory data (outside the root DSE) of a non-public directory must be configured to prevent anonymous access.","fix_text":"Configure directory data (outside the root DSE) of a non-public directory to prevent anonymous access.\n\nFor AD, there are multiple configuration items that could enable anonymous access.\n\nChanging the access permissions on the domain naming context object (from the secure defaults) could enable anonymous access. If the check procedures indicate this is the cause, the process that was used to change the permissions should be reversed. This could have been through the Windows Support Tools ADSI Edit console (adsiedit.msc).\n\nThe dsHeuristics option is used. This is addressed in check V-8555 in the AD Forest STIG.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nOpen \"Command Prompt\" (not elevated).\n\nRun \"ldp.exe\".\n\nFrom the \"Connection menu\", select \"Bind\".\n\nClear the User, Password, and Domain fields.\n\nSelect \"Simple bind\" for the Bind type and click \"OK\".\n\nConfirmation of anonymous access will be displayed at the end:\n\nres = ldap_simple_bind_s\nAuthenticated as: 'NT AUTHORITY\\ANONYMOUS LOGON'\n\nFrom the \"Browse\" menu, select \"Search\".\n\nIn the Search dialog, enter the DN of the domain naming context (generally something like \"dc=disaost,dc=mil\") in the Base DN field.\n\nClear the Attributes field and select \"Run\".\n\nError messages should display related to Bind and user not authenticated.\n\nIf attribute data is displayed, anonymous access is enabled to the domain naming context and this is a finding.\n\nThe following network controls allow the finding severity to be downgraded to a CAT II since these measures lower the risk associated with anonymous access.\n\nNetwork hardware ports at the site are subject to 802.1x authentication or MAC address restrictions. \n\nPremise firewall or host restrictions prevent access to ports 389, 636, 3268, and 3269 from client hosts not explicitly identified by domain (.mil) or IP address.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"To the extent that anonymous access to directory data (outside the root DSE) is permitted, read access control of the data is effectively disabled. If other means of controlling access (such as network restrictions) are compromised, there may be nothing else to protect the confidentiality of sensitive directory data.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-103359","V-93271","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9277","uuid":"ee9a5c21-03c7-47cb-babc-b6f68c95d092","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D6E8F708369005DCF3E65A04E97842AB46031232\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2019 directory data (outside the root DSE) of a non-public directory must be configured to prevent anonymous access.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205876","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205876","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205876","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205876r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205876","rule_version":"WN19-DC-000330","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 domain controllers must be configured to allow reset of machine account passwords.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Domain controller: Refuse machine account password changes\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: RefusePasswordChange\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enabling this setting on all domain controllers in a domain prevents domain members from changing their computer account passwords. If these passwords are weak or compromised, the inability to change them may leave these computers vulnerable.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-93273","SV-103361","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9881","uuid":"64fb6fe5-b656-4092-bd7d-f12e025a5d64","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1D3FEDD3DAF067F78B8B603A378A3DF3F2E4034F\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2019 domain controllers must be configured to allow reset of machine account passwords.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205877","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205877","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205877","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205877r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205877","rule_version":"WN19-DC-000430","rule_title":"The password for the krbtgt account on a domain must be reset at least every 180 days.","fix_text":"Reset the password for the krbtgt account a least every 180 days. The password must be changed twice to effectively remove the password history. Changing once, waiting for replication to complete and changing again reduces the risk of issues. Changing twice in rapid succession forces clients to reauthenticate (including application services) but is desired if a compromise is suspected.\n\nPowerShell scripts are available to accomplish this such as at the following link:\n\nhttps://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/answers/questions/97108/resetting-the-krbtgt-account-password-in-a-domain.html\n\nAll scripts should be tested.\n\nOpen \"Active Directory Users and Computers\" (available from various menus or run \"dsa.msc\").\n\nSelect \"Advanced Features\" in the \"View\" menu if not previously selected.\n\nSelect the \"Users\" node.\n\nRight-click on the krbtgt account and select \"Reset password\".\n\nEnter a password that meets password complexity requirements.\n\nClear the \"User must change password at next logon\" check box.\n\nThe system will automatically change this to a system-generated complex password.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This requirement is applicable to domain controllers; it is NA for other systems. \n\nOpen \"Windows PowerShell\".\n\nEnter \"Get-ADUser krbtgt -Property PasswordLastSet\".\n\nIf the \"PasswordLastSet\" date is more than 180 days old, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The krbtgt account acts as a service account for the Kerberos Key Distribution Center (KDC) service.  The account and password are created when a domain is created and the password is typically not changed.  If the krbtgt account is compromised, attackers can create valid Kerberos Ticket Granting Tickets (TGT).\n\nThe password must be changed twice to effectively remove the password history. Changing once, waiting for replication to complete and the amount of time equal to or greater than the maximum Kerberos ticket lifetime, and changing again reduces the risk of issues.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-93211","SV-103299","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"7733","uuid":"82eac84f-a41d-48a1-b316-c435efecdd33","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D4FCDA33BE0DC34AC87CE829746089291F6D8BE0\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The password for the krbtgt account on a domain must be reset at least every 180 days.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205906","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205906","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205906","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205906r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205906","rule_version":"WN19-MS-000050","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 must limit the caching of logon credentials to four or less on domain-joined member servers.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Interactive Logon: Number of previous logons to cache (in case Domain Controller is not available)\" to \"4\" logons or less.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to member servers. For domain controllers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Winlogon\\\n\nValue Name:  CachedLogonsCount\n\nValue Type:  REG_SZ\nValue:  4 (or less)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The default Windows configuration caches the last logon credentials for users who log on interactively to a system. This feature is provided for system availability reasons, such as the user's machine being disconnected from the network or domain controllers being unavailable. Even though the credential cache is well protected, if a system is attacked, an unauthorized individual may isolate the password to a domain user account using a password-cracking program and gain access to the domain.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-103363","V-93275","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5636","uuid":"51efc8c4-b9bc-4473-8cfb-c1f4923f00c7","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A9EB08169CBDFD3E955E193755E84B399BDFE1CC\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2019 must limit the caching of logon credentials to four or less on domain-joined member servers.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205907","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205907","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205907","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205907r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205907","rule_version":"WN19-MS-000140","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 must be running Credential Guard on domain-joined member servers.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Device Guard >> \"Turn On Virtualization Based Security\" to \"Enabled\" with \"Enabled with UEFI lock\" selected for \"Credential Guard Configuration\".\n\nA Microsoft article on Credential Guard system requirement can be found at the following link:\n\nhttps://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/security/identity-protection/credential-guard/credential-guard-requirements\n\nSeverity Override Guidance: The AO can allow the severity override if they have reviewed the overall protection provided to the affected servers that are not capable of complying with the Credential Guard requirement. Items that should be reviewed/considered for compliance or mitigation for non-Credential Guard compliance are:\n\nThe use of Microsoft Local Administrator Password Solution (LAPS) or similar products to control different local administrative passwords for all affected servers. This is to include a strict password change requirement (60 days or less).\n\u2026.\nStrict separation of roles and duties. Server administrator credentials cannot be used on Windows 10 desktop to administer it. Documentation of all exceptions should be supplied.\n\u2026.\nUse of a Privileged Access Workstation (PAW) and adherence to the Clean Source principle for administering affected servers. \n\u2026.\nBoundary Protection that is currently in place to protect from vulnerabilities in the network/servers.\n\u2026.\nWindows Defender rule block credential stealing from LSASS.exe is applied.  This rule can only be applied if Windows Defender is in use.\n\u2026.\nThe overall number of vulnerabilities that are unmitigated on the network/servers.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"For domain controllers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems, this is NA.\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\" with elevated privileges (run as administrator).\n\nEnter the following:\n\n\"Get-CimInstance -ClassName Win32_DeviceGuard -Namespace root\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DeviceGuard\"\n\nIf \"SecurityServicesRunning\" does not include a value of \"1\" (e.g., \"{1, 2}\"), this is a finding.\n\nAlternately:\n\nRun \"System Information\".\n\nUnder \"System Summary\", verify the following:\n\nIf \"Device Guard Security Services Running\" does not list \"Credential Guard\", this is a finding.\n\nThe policy settings referenced in the Fix section will configure the following registry value. However, due to hardware requirements, the registry value alone does not ensure proper function.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DeviceGuard\\\n\nValue Name: LsaCfgFlags\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1) (Enabled with UEFI lock)\n\nA Microsoft article on Credential Guard system requirement can be found at the following link:\n\nhttps://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/security/identity-protection/credential-guard/credential-guard-requirements","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Credential Guard uses virtualization-based security to protect data that could be used in credential theft attacks if compromised. This authentication information, which was stored in the Local Security Authority (LSA) in previous versions of Windows, is isolated from the rest of operating system and can only be accessed by privileged system software.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-93277","SV-103365","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"3577","uuid":"0136e0df-e1dd-4b6a-9857-dd352ae5222f","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F8467DE96EFBA17D01E2C002A5935CD00848E59B\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2019 must be running Credential Guard on domain-joined member servers.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205908","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205908","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205908","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205908r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205908","rule_version":"WN19-SO-000020","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 must prevent local accounts with blank passwords from being used from the network.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Accounts: Limit local account use of blank passwords to console logon only\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: LimitBlankPasswordUse\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"An account without a password can allow unauthorized access to a system as only the username would be required. Password policies should prevent accounts with blank passwords from existing on a system. However, if a local account with a blank password does exist, enabling this setting will prevent network access, limiting the account to local console logon only.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-93279","SV-103367","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"6446","uuid":"cf4e56a2-d062-4957-bcb1-6465c6e968bd","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: B95FA8A2157282F3BC662A7DC9832F4548EEA5C5\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2019 must prevent local accounts with blank passwords from being used from the network.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205909","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205909","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205909","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205909r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205909","rule_version":"WN19-SO-000030","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 built-in administrator account must be renamed.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Accounts: Rename administrator account\" to a name other than \"Administrator\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Accounts: Rename administrator account\" is not set to a value other than \"Administrator\", this is a finding.\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas SecurityPolicy /CFG C:\\Path\\FileName.Txt\n\nIf \"NewAdministratorName\" is not something other than \"Administrator\" in the file, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The built-in administrator account is a well-known account subject to attack. Renaming this account to an unidentified name improves the protection of this account and the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-93281","SV-103369","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4775","uuid":"27492771-c74a-4117-8b8c-8941dc805d93","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 0D7DC265C8F4AA47EEF3B32508D50A3376B64F9E\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2019 built-in administrator account must be renamed.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205910","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205910","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205910","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205910r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205910","rule_version":"WN19-SO-000040","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 built-in guest account must be renamed.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Accounts: Rename guest account\" to a name other than \"Guest\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Accounts: Rename guest account\" is not set to a value other than \"Guest\", this is a finding.\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas SecurityPolicy /CFG C:\\Path\\FileName.Txt\n\nIf \"NewGuestName\" is not something other than \"Guest\" in the file, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The built-in guest account is a well-known user account on all Windows systems and, as initially installed, does not require a password. This can allow access to system resources by unauthorized users. Renaming this account to an unidentified name improves the protection of this account and the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-103371","V-93283","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5465","uuid":"df3bc8d7-ab29-4200-b209-25cc8aa256ac","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1304F0AB4C6DAAC2470FDCF3CE54ABCD43599CA8\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2019 built-in guest account must be renamed.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205911","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205911","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205911","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205911r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205911","rule_version":"WN19-SO-000100","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 maximum age for machine account passwords must be configured to 30 days or less.","fix_text":"This is the default configuration for this setting (30 days).\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Domain member: Maximum machine account password age\" to \"30\" or less (excluding \"0\", which is unacceptable).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is the default configuration for this setting (30 days).\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: MaximumPasswordAge\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x0000001e (30) (or less, but not 0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Computer account passwords are changed automatically on a regular basis. This setting controls the maximum password age that a machine account may have. This must be set to no more than 30 days, ensuring the machine changes its password monthly.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-103373","V-93285","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"6516","uuid":"20e3af48-6f9a-4110-b426-0908a1cf3d27","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: B36841E0F6412AC2353BEED588BBB77308E8748B\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2019 maximum age for machine account passwords must be configured to 30 days or less.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205912","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205912","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205912","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205912r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205912","rule_version":"WN19-SO-000150","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 Smart Card removal option must be configured to Force Logoff or Lock Workstation.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Interactive logon: Smart card removal behavior\" to \"Lock Workstation\" or \"Force Logoff\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Winlogon\\\n \nValue Name: scremoveoption\n\nValue Type: REG_SZ\nValue: 1 (Lock Workstation) or 2 (Force Logoff)\n\nIf configuring this on servers causes issues, such as terminating users' remote sessions, and the organization has a policy in place that any other sessions on the servers, such as administrative console logons, are manually locked or logged off when unattended or not in use, this would be acceptable. This must be documented with the ISSO.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unattended systems are susceptible to unauthorized use and must be locked. Configuring a system to lock when a smart card is removed will ensure the system is inaccessible when unattended.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-93287","SV-103375","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"6974","uuid":"d0f943d4-a95b-4e99-8d8c-65c501fc2506","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-205913","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205913","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205913","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205913r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205913","rule_version":"WN19-SO-000210","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 must not allow anonymous SID/Name translation.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network access: Allow anonymous SID/Name translation\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Network access: Allow anonymous SID/Name translation\" is not set to \"Disabled\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing anonymous SID/Name translation can provide sensitive information for accessing a system. Only authorized users must be able to perform such translations.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-103377","V-93289","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"6690","uuid":"a9b4139e-61ea-4449-8b2b-5d09e398f247","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1DD74078EB4BD8708149949BE3DB7C4F27AE2E06\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2019 must not allow anonymous SID/Name translation.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205914","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205914","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205914","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205914r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205914","rule_version":"WN19-SO-000220","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 must not allow anonymous enumeration of Security Account Manager (SAM) accounts.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network access: Do not allow anonymous enumeration of SAM accounts\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: RestrictAnonymousSAM\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Anonymous enumeration of SAM accounts allows anonymous logon users (null session connections) to list all accounts names, thus providing a list of potential points to attack the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-93291","SV-103379","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4645","uuid":"d2a0f744-3920-4be3-bad8-d301221b5574","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: B34B9BA35C4048E1E2CE4FFAE5D490A1C0B2581E\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2019 must not allow anonymous enumeration of Security Account Manager (SAM) accounts.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205915","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205915","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205915","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205915r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205915","rule_version":"WN19-SO-000240","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 must be configured to prevent anonymous users from having the same permissions as the Everyone group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network access: Let Everyone permissions apply to anonymous users\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: EveryoneIncludesAnonymous\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Access by anonymous users must be restricted. If this setting is enabled, anonymous users have the same rights and permissions as the built-in Everyone group. Anonymous users must not have these permissions or rights.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","