gain unauthorized access if allowed to authenticate anonymously versus using the computer identity.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-103383","V-93295","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"8430","uuid":"9566d845-0e34-4a3c-b696-a11bd227fa37","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9003D7BCCCA51B639A7B6A3807161237DB47A95B\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2019 services using Local System that use Negotiate when reverting to NTLM authentication must use the computer identity instead of authenticating anonymously.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205917","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205917","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205917","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205917r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205917","rule_version":"WN19-SO-000270","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 must prevent NTLM from falling back to a Null session.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network security: Allow LocalSystem NULL session fallback\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\LSA\\MSV1_0\\\n\nValue Name: allownullsessionfallback\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"NTLM sessions that are allowed to fall back to Null (unauthenticated) sessions may gain unauthorized access.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-93297","SV-103385","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5900","uuid":"ea2135ac-ea73-4c9d-bbd5-dd48be9ebd02","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D7F33CDF3455979406C1331DD493223FBE7441E9\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2019 must prevent NTLM from falling back to a Null session.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205918","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205918","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205918","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205918r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205918","rule_version":"WN19-SO-000280","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 must prevent PKU2U authentication using online identities.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network security: Allow PKU2U authentication requests to this computer to use online identities\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\LSA\\pku2u\\\n\nValue Name: AllowOnlineID\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"PKU2U is a peer-to-peer authentication protocol. This setting prevents online identities from authenticating to domain-joined systems. Authentication will be centrally managed with Windows user accounts.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-103387","V-93299","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"8014","uuid":"91db8f2c-0365-4cc3-b1f7-f4e0650d824d","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9B2B3101B1476279155E278411BD0706CDE4D737\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2019 must prevent PKU2U authentication using online identities.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205919","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205919","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205919","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205919r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205919","rule_version":"WN19-SO-000310","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 LAN Manager authentication level must be configured to send NTLMv2 response only and to refuse LM and NTLM.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network security: LAN Manager authentication level\" to \"Send NTLMv2 response only. Refuse LM & NTLM\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: LmCompatibilityLevel\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000005 (5)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Kerberos v5 authentication protocol is the default for authentication of users who are logging on to domain accounts. NTLM, which is less secure, is retained in later Windows versions for compatibility with clients and servers that are running earlier versions of Windows or applications that still use it. It is also used to authenticate logons to standalone or nondomain-joined computers that are running later versions.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-103389","V-93301","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"8879","uuid":"cecee944-55b8-4ff6-a29c-7408272615bd","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 5EFD580997A11941A6BBE92DDF8E645C63A89968\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2019 LAN Manager authentication level must be configured to send NTLMv2 response only and to refuse LM and NTLM.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205920","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205920","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205920","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205920r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205920","rule_version":"WN19-SO-000320","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 must be configured to at least negotiate signing for LDAP client signing.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network security: LDAP client signing requirements\" to \"Negotiate signing\" at a minimum.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LDAP\\\n\nValue Name: LDAPClientIntegrity\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting controls the signing requirements for LDAP clients. This must be set to \"Negotiate signing\" or \"Require signing\", depending on the environment and type of LDAP server in use.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-103391","V-93303","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"2818","uuid":"0f574bfe-3fe6-4b07-9179-a3bb8ee514bd","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 0DDA7EE28DAB50509B2B14C47E61559FDD2C8365\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2019 must be configured to at least negotiate signing for LDAP client signing.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205921","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205921","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205921","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205921r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205921","rule_version":"WN19-SO-000330","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 session security for NTLM SSP-based clients must be configured to require NTLMv2 session security and 128-bit encryption.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network security: Minimum session security for NTLM SSP based (including secure RPC) clients\" to \"Require NTLMv2 session security\" and \"Require 128-bit encryption\" (all options selected).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\MSV1_0\\\n\nValue Name: NTLMMinClientSec\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x20080000 (537395200)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Microsoft has implemented a variety of security support providers for use with Remote Procedure Call (RPC) sessions. All of the options must be enabled to ensure the maximum security level.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-103393","V-93305","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5251","uuid":"769e4b3b-b6a3-40d4-ab12-36ecdae3383a","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FF3C8E2BEBB37A2352629E1167793C2552B48AE7\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2019 session security for NTLM SSP-based clients must be configured to require NTLMv2 session security and 128-bit encryption.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205922","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205922","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205922","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205922r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205922","rule_version":"WN19-SO-000340","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 session security for NTLM SSP-based servers must be configured to require NTLMv2 session security and 128-bit encryption.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"Network security: Minimum session security for NTLM SSP based (including secure RPC) servers\" to \"Require NTLMv2 session security\" and \"Require 128-bit encryption\" (all options selected).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\MSV1_0\\\n\nValue Name: NTLMMinServerSec\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x20080000 (537395200)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Microsoft has implemented a variety of security support providers for use with Remote Procedure Call (RPC) sessions. All of the options must be enabled to ensure the maximum security level.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-103395","V-93307","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"7174","uuid":"f4b1b65e-0308-4278-becc-ecdbf8172338","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9916288F1C0CF073E2E0E9A0831ECCFF95220F6D\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2019 session security for NTLM SSP-based servers must be configured to require NTLMv2 session security and 128-bit encryption.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205923","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205923","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205923","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205923r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205923","rule_version":"WN19-SO-000370","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 default permissions of global system objects must be strengthened.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> \"System objects: Strengthen default permissions of internal system objects (e.g., Symbolic Links)\" to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Session Manager\\\n\nValue Name: ProtectionMode\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Windows systems maintain a global list of shared system resources such as DOS device names, mutexes, and semaphores. Each type of object is created with a default Discretionary Access Control List (DACL) that specifies who can access the objects with what permissions. When this policy is enabled, the default DACL is stronger, allowing non-administrative users to read shared objects but not to modify shared objects they did not create.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-93309","SV-103397","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"2570","uuid":"5f095788-c946-4f9f-8e23-8a363b950f81","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F61BA896E9DEC1F787F819D9D09587C780DC49C7\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2019 default permissions of global system objects must be strengthened.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205924","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205924","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205924","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-205924r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-205924","rule_version":"WN19-UC-000010","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 must preserve zone information when saving attachments.","fix_text":"The default behavior is for Windows to mark file attachments with their zone information.\n\nIf this needs to be corrected, configure the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Attachment Manager >> \"Do not preserve zone information in file attachments\" to \"Not Configured\" or \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The default behavior is for Windows to mark file attachments with their zone information.\n\nIf the registry Value Name below does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"2\", this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"1\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Attachments\\\n\nValue Name: SaveZoneInformation\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000002 (2) (or if the Value Name does not exist)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Attachments from outside sources may contain malicious code. Preserving zone of origin (Internet, intranet, local, restricted) information on file attachments allows Windows to determine risk.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-103399","V-93311","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1389","uuid":"ef603cc6-7583-4326-8a5b-31924594a98d","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A4E226BF3169A410A58EB16860E664B3CB511FCB\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2019 must preserve zone information when saving attachments.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-205925","group_tree":[{"id":"V-205925","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00229","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-205925","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00229","rule_id_src":"SV-205925r991591_rule","rule_id":"SV-205925","rule_version":"WN19-CC-000450","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 must disable automatically signing in the last interactive user after a system-initiated restart.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Logon Options >> \"Sign-in last interactive user automatically after a system-initiated restart\" to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the registry value below. If it does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: DisableAutomaticRestartSignOn\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Windows can be configured to automatically sign the user back in after a Windows Update restart. Some protections are in place to help ensure this is done in a secure fashion; however, disabling this will prevent the caching of credentials for this purpose and also ensure the user is aware of the restart.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["SV-103357","V-93269","CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5677","uuid":"25ceea51-ade9-4227-bbbe-1894476b9365","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7269E16E61A096415ED13D23A87ED5A2B058A5F4\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2019 must disable automatically signing in the last interactive user after a system-initiated restart.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-214936","group_tree":[{"id":"V-214936","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-214936","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-214936r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-214936","rule_version":"WN19-00-000280","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 must have a host-based firewall installed and enabled.","fix_text":"Install and enable a host-based firewall on the system.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Determine if a host-based firewall is installed and enabled on the system.\n\nIf a host-based firewall is not installed and enabled on the system, this is a finding.\n\nThe configuration requirements will be determined by the applicable firewall STIG.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A firewall provides a line of defense against attack, allowing or blocking inbound and outbound connections based on a set of rules.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["V-93571","SV-103657","CCI-000366","CCI-002080"],"reference_identifier":"7232","uuid":"153afe86-7a6d-4317-9bca-91ff02a8a08e","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 34358CE779923D24DCC3F393874B86419126C51F\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Windows Server 2019 must have a host-based firewall installed and enabled.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-257503","group_tree":[{"id":"V-257503","title":"SRG-OS-000041-GPOS-00019","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-257503","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000041-GPOS-00019","rule_id_src":"SV-257503r958420_rule","rule_id":"SV-257503","rule_version":"WN19-CC-000530","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 must have PowerShell Transcription enabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows PowerShell >> \"Turn on PowerShell Transcription\" to \"Enabled\".\n\nSpecify the Transcript output directory to point to a Central Log Server or another secure location to prevent user access.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\PowerShell\\Transcription\\\n\nValue Name: EnableTranscripting\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nEnabling PowerShell Transcription will record detailed information from the processing of PowerShell commands and scripts. This can provide additional detail when malware has run on a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000134"],"reference_identifier":"6695","uuid":"bfc70957-49b6-4109-8d0e-167da2cb45b7","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-271428","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271428","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271428","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-271428r1137691_rule","rule_id":"SV-271428","rule_version":"WN19-DC-000391","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 must be configured for certificate-based authentication for domain controllers.","fix_text":"Configure the registry value.\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Kdc\n \nValue Name: StrongCertificateBindingEnforcement\n \nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1) or 0x00000002 (2)","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. This is not applicable for member servers.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Kdc\n \nValue Name: StrongCertificateBindingEnforcement\n \nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1) or 0x00000002 (2)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Active Directory domain services elevation of privilege vulnerability could allow a user rights to the system, such as administrative and other high-level capabilities.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"2844","uuid":"0cecbf68-6d6d-4e9b-8f52-b340c5964183","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 70F4A9BA5C3E9937716B8E5A5964C6C00C6E316E\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2019 must be configured for certificate-based authentication for domain controllers.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271429","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271429","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271429","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-271429r1137691_rule","rule_id":"SV-271429","rule_version":"WN19-DC-000401","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 must be configured for named-based strong mappings for certificates.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Template >> System >> KDC >> Allow name-based strong mappings for certificates to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. This is not applicable for member servers.\n\nVerify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\nOr\nUsing the registry, check HKLM\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\KDC\\Parameters, Key: UseStrongNameMatches.                      \nOr\nUsing GPRESULT, check the applicable GPO for \"Allow name-based strong mappings for certificates\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Administrative Template >> System >> KDC >> Allow name-based strong mappings for certificates.\n\nIf \"Allow name-based strong mappings for certificates\" is not \"Enabled\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Weak mappings give rise to security vulnerabilities and demand hardening measures. Certificate names must be correctly mapped to the intended user account in Active Directory. A lack of strong name-based mappings allows certain weak certificate mappings, such as Issuer/Subject AltSecID and User Principal Names (UPN) mappings, to be treated as strong mappings.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"5826","uuid":"c197dfcd-79fc-4366-b4f1-35c43d3ade1f","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 5CEC8C9C387898518E5240E03471F76718409B51\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2019 must be configured for named-based strong mappings for certificates.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-278934","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278934","title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278934","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","rule_id_src":"SV-278934r1135330_rule","rule_id":"SV-278934","rule_version":"WN19-AU-000581","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 must be configured to audit file system failures.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Object Access >> \"Audit File System\" with \"Failure\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that Audit File System auditing has been enabled: \n\nComputer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Object Access >> Audit File System.\n\nIf \"Audit File System\" is not set to \"Failure\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior. Credential validation records events related to validation tests on credentials for a user account logon.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"3795","uuid":"564d41f1-ab15-4a6d-9e6b-1f352c03a6e5","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8221C3B2897513ABF7729C7D42E0B94E4A99903C\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2019 must be configured to audit file system failures.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-278935","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278935","title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278935","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","rule_id_src":"SV-278935r1135333_rule","rule_id":"SV-278935","rule_version":"WN19-AU-000582","rule_title":"Windows Server 2019 must be configured to audit file system successes.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Object Access >> \"Audit File System\" with \"Success\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that Audit File System auditing has been enabled: \n\nComputer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Object Access >> Audit File System. \n\nIf \"Audit File System\" is not set to \"Success\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2019_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior. Credential validation records events related to validation tests on credentials for a user account logon.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"3717","uuid":"93d98323-fbed-4338-ac42-d4b4db0193c4","stig_uuid":"f3bd6f6a-e22d-458d-8a9e-0a127efa543e","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2019_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 3DA9AB7A83F55B01DC3DF50F89ED41C7E42D7B17\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2019 must be configured to audit file system successes.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2019 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-278936","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278936","title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278936","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","rule_id_src":"SV-278936r1135336_rule","rule_id":"SV-278936","rule_versi